            <h3 data-uuid="bc8861ed4df24c47964ec4f216014922">Part
                2: Write an Explanatory Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="60fb8b9b84d84b32933d9def1e0a8e41">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="3ba6b1afcbea46da84d8ad84abe51084">The time of Andrew Jacksonâ€™s presidency, also called
                the Age of Jackson, was a time of regional differences and political changes. At first many people saw Andrew Jackson as a representative of everyday people.
                Soon tensions between the North and South led to tariff regulations. This led
                to the nullification crisis in which Jackson upheld federal authority. He did
                not always support greater federal power. For example, he opposed the Second
                Bank of the United States. President Jackson also did not make the state of
                Georgia follow the ruling of the Supreme Court in <i>Worcester </i>v.<i> Georgia.</i> This led to removal of the Cherokees to the
                Indian Territory and the Trail of Tears.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="6d7612722d244339a5b9903ccdb9574e">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="7130b46855574434a054c6f61e5be40a">The Age of Jackson was a time of many controversies,
                including tensions between the regions of the country, the state and federal governments, and Native Americans and white settlers. Write an explanatory essay about the Age of Jackson.</p>
            <p data-uuid="4f1e9a45bb2c4c96bcfff255b8f04d90">Complete the following steps as you
                plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="7b44c0822e9342048c846c225404c40a">
                <li data-uuid="855497bda3af40339950b5d27de8fd13">Review your notes and sources before you start writing.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="c7448b81d7e64ed2804ef50646859b88">Use at least <i>two&#160;</i>of the
                    sources in Part 1, and develop the topic with relevant, well-chosen text
                    evidence from the documents.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="049fe6f2c4704b2b9f6f92343bcd4d7a">Cite specific text evidence from each of the sources in your
                    response.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="ebfb156cab194497ada149b8134aa418">Plan your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body
                    paragraphs, and a concluding paragraph.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="0f5c16ec4b2b4ad3921fb96885b08f89">Establish a formal tone and use transitions to improve the flow of your writing, connect ideas, and clarify meaning.</li>
                <li data-uuid="db376e2374334b99ad03bc3b6c257b85">Organize your essay in a clear way that focuses on the topic and supports it with well-chosen facts, details, and examples.</li>
                <li data-uuid="d293f4e6af134f2a84b2e44e5cd0e6e2">Use precise, descriptive language and social studies terms to explain your topic.</li>
                <li data-uuid="0ddaec91b0224be5bb9190ca572467e5">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
